1:
Sin speaks like an oracle in the heart of the wicked man;
\q there is no fear of God in his eyes.
\q

3:
His words are sinful and deceitful;
\q he does not want to be wise and do good.
\q

4:
While he lies in bed, he plans ways to sin;
\q he sets out on an evil way;
\q he does not reject evil.

5:
Your covenant faithfulness, Yahweh, reaches to the heavens;
\q your loyalty reaches to the clouds.
\q

6:
Your righteousness is like the mountains of God;
\q your judgments are like the great deep.
\q Yahweh, you preserve both mankind and the animals.

8:
They will be abundantly satisfied with the richness of the food of your house;
\q you will let them drink from the river of your precious blessings.
\q
